    {
      "text": "Bio-Magical Zones, or BMZs, are mysterious areas in the world where animals gradually transform into monster girls. These zones have a unique energy signature and defy conventional physics and biology. While their origins remain unknown, their impact on the world is significant, affecting economics, politics, and society.",
      "contextConfig": {
        "prefix": "----\n",
        "suffix": "\n",
        "tokenBudget": 1,
        "reservedTokens": 0,
        "budgetPriority": 26,
        "trimDirection": "trimBottom",
        "insertionType": "newline",
        "maximumTrimType": "sentence",
        "insertionPosition": -1
      },
      "lastUpdatedAt": 1737176067513,
      "displayName": "Bio-Magical Zones",
      "id": "441c53e3-7fd1-4060-8e3d-9b793de51e54",
      "keys": [
        "BMZ",
        "BMZs",
        "Bio-Magical Zones",
        "Zones",
        "Zone"
      ],
      "searchRange": 1000,
      "enabled": true,
      "forceActivation": false,
      "keyRelative": false,
      "nonStoryActivatable": false,
      "category": "bdea752e-b8f6-4b34-90fa-29404433294a",
      "loreBiasGroups": [
        {
          "phrases": [],
          "ensureSequenceFinish": false,
          "generateOnce": true,
          "bias": 0,
          "enabled": true,
          "whenInactive": false
        }
      ],
      "advancedConditions": []
    },
    {
      "text": "The Cascade Valley BMZ is a unique and isolated area, approximately 150 miles in diameter, located east of the Cascade Mountains in the Pacific Northwest. This Bio-Magical Zone is characterized by its diverse microclimates and varied terrain, encompassing mountains, valleys, rivers, and lakes. Its natural boundaries and the shimmering barrier that surrounds it create a sense of seclusion and mystery.\n\nThe valley enjoys a protected microclimate with four distinct seasons: a rainy and mild spring ideal for newborn monster girls, warm summers with cool nights perfect for production, an extended harvest season in the fall, and winters with light snow that require less protection for monster girls compared to regular livestock. Abundant water sources, including mountain streams, natural springs, seasonal creeks, and underground aquifers, support the diverse ecosystem and agricultural activities within the zone.",
      "contextConfig": {
        "prefix": "----\n",
        "suffix": "\n",
        "tokenBudget": 1,
        "reservedTokens": 0,
        "budgetPriority": 26,
        "trimDirection": "trimBottom",
        "insertionType": "newline",
        "maximumTrimType": "sentence",
        "insertionPosition": -1
      },
      "lastUpdatedAt": 1737176203902,
      "displayName": "Cascade Valley BMZ",
      "id": "6da7cba6-8496-4768-90f2-2eb9b9880a79",
      "keys": [
        "Cascade Valley BMZ",
        "BMZ",
        "Zone"
      ],
      "searchRange": 1000,
      "enabled": true,
      "forceActivation": false,
      "keyRelative": false,
      "nonStoryActivatable": false,
      "category": "1825835f-876b-4a55-8865-998391b40ad8",
      "loreBiasGroups": [
        {
          "phrases": [],
          "ensureSequenceFinish": false,
          "generateOnce": true,
          "bias": 0,
          "enabled": true,
          "whenInactive": false
        }
      ],
      "advancedConditions": []
    },
    {
      "text": "The major settlement with a population of 12,000, serving as the main market town for monster girl products. It boasts processing facilities, an agricultural college specializing in monster girl care, a renowned farmer's market, and tourist attractions. Summit Grove acts as the gateway to the rest of the Cascade Valley BMZ.",
      "contextConfig": {
        "prefix": "----\n",
        "suffix": "\n",
        "tokenBudget": 1,
        "reservedTokens": 0,
        "budgetPriority": 26,
        "trimDirection": "trimBottom",
        "insertionType": "newline",
        "maximumTrimType": "sentence",
        "insertionPosition": -1
      },
      "lastUpdatedAt": 1737176579656,
      "displayName": "Summit Grove",
